article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 76, Austin Peay 73
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. (AP) -- Jason McLeish hit a 3-pointer with a minute left Thursday night and Eastern Kentucky held on to beat Austin Peay 76-73. McLeish scored all but two of his 28 points in the second half for Eastern (14-14, 11-8 Ohio Valley Conference). The Colonels won their fourth straight conference contest. Zac Schlader led the Governors (16-13, 10-9) with 16 points. Maurice Hampton and Fernandez Lockett had 14 each, and Derek Wright scored 10. McLeish's 3-pointer with 1:03 left in the game turned a 66-64 deficit into a 67-66 lead. Earlier, he connected on three consecutive 3-pointers in a 15-5 run that gave the Colonels a 46-45 lead with 10:42 left. Darnell Dialls and Michael Brock added 13 points each for the Colonels. Brock scored seven of Easterns first nine points.
